in fact , the persistence of strong reservations about both Royal and Sarkozy helps explain the surge in popularity for a third candidate , Francois Bayrou , a traditional centrist , pro-European politician . Bayrou has never had it so good , but , barring the unlikely collapse of one of the two leading candidates ’ campaigns , he will fail to qualify for the second-round runoff .
