poll after poll shows that Latins feel more negatively about the US than at any time since the 1960 &apos;s . in contrast to that era , popular hostility is not really motivated by US actions in or toward Latin America ; but today &apos;s anti-Americanism still complicates life greatly for democratic leaders in the hemisphere , and for America itself .
