what Next for Europe ?
it began well , when Spanish voters approved the draft European Union constitution , but it turned sour when French and Dutch voters spurned it soon after . those votes partly reflected displeasure with domestic policies , and partly disappointment with the way governments conduct European affairs .
within days of the votes , they failed to agree on the EU budget for 2007-13 . French and British leaders engaged in a heated quarrel that derailed the subsequent summit , before Britain assumed the rotating six-month EU presidency in July .
besides burying the draft constitution , it has largely sidestepped the budget issue . chances that it gets the budget approved this year are slim , and , unless the dispute is resolved soon , the Union will not have an operational budget by 2007 .
